<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 79/373/EEC of 2 April 1979 on the marketing of compound feedingstuffs (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 97/47/EC (2), and in particular Article 10(e) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 2. aprilli 1979. aasta direktiivi 79/373/EM&Uuml; (segas&ouml;&ouml;tade turustamise kohta, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni direktiiviga 97/47/E&Uuml; (2)), eriti selle artikli 10 punkti e, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, under point VII.E.4 of Annex XV to the Act of Accession, the Kingdom of Sweden may maintain its national legislation making it compulsory to state the phosphorus content on the labelling of compound feedingstuffs intended for fish until 31 December 1997; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: &uuml;hinemisakti XV lisa VII osa E jao l&otilde;ike 4 alusel v&otilde;ib Rootsi Kuningriik 31. detsembrini 1997 j&otilde;usse j&auml;tta siseriiklikud &otilde;igusaktid, milles s&auml;testatakse fosforisisalduse m&auml;rkimine kalade jaoks etten&auml;htud segas&ouml;&ouml;da etikettidele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, under Annex XV of the abovementioned Act, Sweden is required to accompany requests for the adaptation of the Community legislation for the mineral concerned by a detailed scientific statement of reasons; </inglise>
<eesti> eespool nimetatud akti XV lisa alusel peab Rootsi lisama &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide kohandamist k&auml;sitlevatele taotlustele asjaomase mineraali puhul &uuml;ksikasjaliku teadusliku p&otilde;hjenduse; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Sweden transmitted a statement of reasons on 5 June 1997; </inglise>
<eesti> Rootsi on edastanud p&otilde;hjenduse 5. juunil 1997; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Directive 79/373/EEC provides for the regular updating of the Annex thereto in the light of scientific and technical knowledge; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiiviga 79/373/EM&Uuml; n&auml;hakse ette k&otilde;nealuse direktiivi lisa korrap&auml;rane ajakohastamine teadusliku ja tehnilise arengu p&otilde;hjal; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas enrichment with phosphorus is disturbing the ecological balance of lakes and seas; whereas eutrophication effects frequently observed in inland lakes are blue-green algae blooms, oxygen deficiency, high fish mortality and reduced biodiversity; </inglise>
<eesti> fosforiga rikastamine h&auml;irib j&auml;rvede ja merede &ouml;koloogilist tasakaalu; sinivetikate &otilde;itsemine, hapnikuvaegus, kalade k&otilde;rge suremus ja v&auml;henenud bioloogiline mitmekesisus on eutrofeerumise m&otilde;ju sisej&auml;rvedele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is therefore necessary to restrict phosphorus emissions to an absolute minimum; whereas the compulsory indication of phosphorus content on the labelling of compound feedingstuffs for fish would make a significant contribution to that objective by facilitating good feeding practice; </inglise>
<eesti> seep&auml;rast on fosfori eraldumine vaja viia miinimumini; fosforisisalduse m&auml;rkimine kalade jaoks etten&auml;htud segas&ouml;&ouml;da etikettidele oleks oluline panus selle eesm&auml;rgi saavutamisel, kuna see h&otilde;lbustaks kasvatajatel kohaldada head s&ouml;&ouml;tmistava; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Directive are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Feedingstuffs, </inglise>
